.TH "devm_fwnode_pwm_get" 9 "devm_fwnode_pwm_get" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_fwnode_pwm_get \- request a resource managed PWM from firmware node
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct pwm_device *" devm_fwnode_pwm_get
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct fwnode_handle *fwnode "  ","
.BI "const char *con_id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device for PWM consumer
.IP "fwnode" 12
firmware node to get the PWM from
.IP "con_id" 12
consumer name
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the PWM device parsed from the firmware node. See \fBof_pwm_get\fP and
\fBacpi_pwm_get\fP for a detailed description.
.SH "RETURN"
A pointer to the requested PWM device or an \fBERR_PTR\fP-encoded
error code on failure.
